 planned out. I'm really quite happy with it and have begun to write it, but I have a problem. In the story are characters whose first languages are, English, German and Japanese respectively. In the story are many situations for them to switch back to their first languages simply because thats the only language they have in common. I'm not sure how to handle the translation in the fic. <br>
<br>
What do you guys think?  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raechasta>Rae Chasta</A> at: 2/2/03 9:37:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pencilsoldier>Pencil Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/2/03 11:12:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.imgmag.com/images/pencil_soldier/EWIC.gif height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple Languages in Fics</span><hr size=1> &lt;write it like hti with the brackets around it&gt;<br>
