<br>
I just want to avoid doing what I have seen way to many times, putting &quot;(in japanese)&quot; at the top of a scene or putting brackets around things that are in a different language while still typing them in english. These both annoy me, they look really amateurish.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirpycho>SirPycho</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://image.com.com/gamespot/images/screenshots/n64/conkersbadfurday/conker_0302_thumb034.jpg hieght=100 width=94" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/19/03 7:36:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image.com.com/gamespot/images/screenshots/n64/conkersbadfurday/conker_0302_thumb034.jpg hieght=64 width=70></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple Languages in Fics</span><hr size=1> If you haven't figured out a way yet here's what you can do:<br>
